Key Match Events: David Fry hit a walk-off home run in the bottom of the tenth to give Cleveland the victory
Post-Match Reflections: Travis Kelce expressed delight after Cleveland's dramatic victory
Kelce wrote on X: 'Playoff baseball baby!!! @CleGuardians have the city absolutely ROCKIN TONIGHT!! What a game!'
Miscellaneous Highlights: Cleveland took a 3-1 lead in the game before surrendering back-to-back home runs to Aaron Judge and Giancarlo Stanton
Outfielder Jhonkensy Noel tied the game with a two-run home run in the ninth inning
The game went into extra innings after a game-tying home run by Jhonkensy Noel
Others: Travis Kelce and Taylor Swift attended Game 1 of the series on Monday night
The Guardians took Game 3 of the ALCS with a 7-5 win
New York Yankees were poised to go 3-0 up in the series when back-to-back home runs helped them into a 5-3 lead before the ninth
